35struct MapEntry
36{
37 uint16_t unicode;
38 uint8_t count;
39 uint8_t charcode;
40};
41
42inline bool operator<(const uint16_t& val, const MapEntry& b) { return val < b.unicode; }

174
175static uint8_t unicodeToCharcode(uint16_t unicode, const MapEntry* entries, size_t entryCount)
176{
177 auto it = std::upper_bound(entries, entries + entryCount, unicode);
178 if (it != entries)
179 {
180 --it;
181 if (unicode < it->unicode + it->count)
182 {
183 return it->charcode + (unicode - it->unicode) + 128;
184 }
185 }
186 throw std::invalid_argument("Unexpected charcode");
187}
188
189static void mapFromUnicode(const std::wstring& str, const MapEntry* entries, size_t entryCount, std::string& bytes)
190{
191 bytes.reserve(str.length());
192 for (wchar_t c : str) {
193 if (c < 0x80) {
194 bytes.push_back(static_cast<char>(c));
195 }
196 else {
197 bytes.push_back(static_cast<char>(unicodeToCharcode(c, entries, entryCount)));
198 }
199 }
200}
201
202#define CONVERT_USING(table, str, bytes) mapFromUnicode(str, table, Size(table), bytes)
203

206void
207TextEncoder::GetBytes(const std::wstring& str, CharacterSet charset, std::string& bytes)
208{
209 bytes.clear();
210
211 switch (charset)
212 {
213 case CharacterSet::Unknown:
214 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_1:
215 bytes.reserve(str.length());
216 for (wchar_t c : str) {
217 if (c <= 0xff) {
218 bytes.push_back(static_cast<char>(c));
219 }
220 else {
221 throw std::invalid_argument("Unexpected charcode");
222 }
223 }
224 break;
225 case CharacterSet::ASCII:
226 {
227 bytes.reserve(str.length());
228 for (wchar_t c : str) {
229 if (c < 0x80) {
230 bytes.push_back(static_cast<char>(c));
231 }
232 else {
233 throw std::invalid_argument("Unexpected charcode");
234 }
235 }
236 break;
237 }
238 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_2:
239 CONVERT_USING(latin2Mapping, str, bytes); break;
240 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_3:
241 CONVERT_USING(latin3Mapping, str, bytes); break;
242 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_4:
243 CONVERT_USING(latin4Mapping, str, bytes); break;
244 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_5:
245 CONVERT_USING(latin5Mapping, str, bytes); break;
246 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_6:
247 CONVERT_USING(latin6Mapping, str, bytes); break;
248 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_7:
249 CONVERT_USING(latin7Mapping, str, bytes); break;
250 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_8:
251 CONVERT_USING(latin8Mapping, str, bytes); break;
252 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_9:
253 CONVERT_USING(latin9Mapping, str, bytes); break;
254 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_10:
255 CONVERT_USING(latin10Mapping, str, bytes); break;
256 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_11:
257 CONVERT_USING(latin11Mapping, str, bytes); break;
258 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_13:
259 CONVERT_USING(latin13Mapping, str, bytes); break;
260 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_14:
261 CONVERT_USING(latin14Mapping, str, bytes); break;
262 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_15:
263 CONVERT_USING(latin15Mapping, str, bytes); break;
264 case CharacterSet::ISO8859_16:
265 CONVERT_USING(latin16Mapping, str, bytes); break;
266 case CharacterSet::Cp437:
267 CONVERT_USING(cp437Mapping, str, bytes); break;
268 case CharacterSet::Cp1250:
269 CONVERT_USING(cp1250Mapping, str, bytes); break;
270 case CharacterSet::Cp1251:
271 CONVERT_USING(cp1251Mapping, str, bytes); break;
272 case CharacterSet::Cp1252:
273 CONVERT_USING(cp1252Mapping, str, bytes); break;
274 case CharacterSet::Cp1256:
275 CONVERT_USING(cp1256Mapping, str, bytes); break;
276 case CharacterSet::Shift_JIS:
277 JPTextEncoder::EncodeShiftJIS(str, bytes); break;
278 case CharacterSet::Big5:
279 Big5TextEncoder::EncodeBig5(str, bytes); break;
280 case CharacterSet::GB2312:
281 GBTextEncoder::EncodeGB2312(str, bytes); break;
282 case CharacterSet::GB18030:
283 GBTextEncoder::EncodeGB18030(str, bytes); break;
284 case CharacterSet::EUC_JP:
285 JPTextEncoder::EncodeEUCJP(str, bytes); break;
286 case CharacterSet::EUC_KR:
287 KRTextDecoder::EncodeEucKr(str, bytes); break;
288 case CharacterSet::UTF8:
289 TextUtfEncoding::ToUtf8(str, bytes); break;
290 default:
291 break;
292 }
